Filtering
=======

## Slides
* Fun intro to filtering
    - Introduce as "blurring"
    - Set of polls: which image is more "blurry"
        - Spatial blur
        - Temporal blur
        - Background blur (zoom meeting)
    - Build up to what "blurry" means
        - We think of it as something that is removing information
            - zoom meeting example
        - But what is it?
            - temporal blur example
                - Play a video
                - Show average of frames
                - it is an "average" of images!
            - Spatial blur example
                - Zoom into an image
                - Cycle through overlaid images, each with a different shift
                - Show average
                - Show which pixels contribute to the value at the pixel in an output
    - All of these example of a more general operation called filtering
        - Bring back original examples
        - Describe the filtering operation with abstract example
            - Animate a 3x3 filter sliding over an image
            - Show entries being multiplied by image entries
            - Show entries being added up
    - What is the filter for spatial averaging?
        - Show original image
        - Spatially averaged images
        - Provide a set of choices
        - Poll results
        - Reveal correct answer
    - What is the filter for temporal blur, when an object is moving left to right
        - Show image
        - Temporally blurred image
        - Poll results
        - Reveal correct answer
    - Designing your own filter
        - Show image
        - Interactive demo that allows you to specify values in different entries
        - Result of filtering operation

